
GIT minimal download and build instructions

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You may already have a version of the bits in e.g. "~/UAL/ual1" (or something similar)
If so, rm -rf them, or rename it.

In "~/UAL" (or similar dirname), using SHELL tcsh, execute the following dashed lines, one at a time (without the - ):

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Get Bits:
      - git clone https://github.com/jtalman/ual1
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Setup Environment:
      - cd ual1
      - setenv UAL `pwd`
      - source setup-linux-ual
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Build:
      - make clean
      - make >&! make.log
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Verify:
      - emacs make.log
              check for errors
              (hopefully just two unimportant vestigial "html errors" that are ignored by make)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Comment:
      You'll likely fine tune this with familiarity.
      A personalized ~/.tcshrc for example.
